nodes.body: Hi @dagurtomas, I think that you'd make this PR easier to review if you split it into three PRs, one for the changes to the low-level topology files and one for each of the added files. The reason is that someone like me would be happy to look at the details of your change that involve dealing with the category theory library, but I really can't say anything about the pure topology bits (as simple as they may seem), which makes me (perhaps unnecessarily) reluctant to review the entire PR.
Done: #10390, #10391 and then this one.

Untested, but the following would refer to more specialized limits API:
```suggestion
noncomputable def finiteCoproduct.cofan : Limits.Cofan X where
```
Here, you should use `Cofan.mk`. (And then, the definition should be labelled with `@[simp]` (or `abbrev`) rather than `@[simps]`.)
Here, you should use `mkCofanColimit`. Then, the `s` you will get will be cofans instead of cocones, so that you may use the syntax `s.inj a` instead of `s.Î¹.app âŸ¨aâŸ©`.
I took the opportunity to apply this suggestion and the previous one in `Profinite/Limits`Â and `CompHaus/Limits` as well

I assume that the `refine âŸ¨fun {F} â†¦ ?_âŸ©` line could be removed, and the syntax `âŸ¨fun {F} â†¦ ?_âŸ©` moved into the suffices block. (By the way `suffices ... by exact ...` can be replaced by `suffices ... from ...`.)

In this definition and a few others, why not declaring the suitable instances for the functor `Profinite.toTopCat` as separate definitions, because it may be useful, rather than having them only inside the proofs?
Are *all* these `{u}` necessary?
Do you think that [#3981](https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/3981) can help here?

I just merged master and tried changing `LightProfiniteMax.{u, w}`Â to `LightProfinite.{max u w}`Â and it didn't work. From the description of the PR you link it sounds like it should though, is mathlib not running on a version of Lean that has this feature?
Indeed it seems that this feature is not in mathlib yet, I guess it will land with `v4.8.0-rc1`? Then we should be able to get rid of all these `TypeMax`, `TopCatMax`, etc. hacks?
Works fine in #12599, waiting for benchmark results
